Privacy Policy

This Privacy Policy, part of our overall Terms of Service, describes how and when AMG collects, uses and shares your information when you use our Service. We will ask for your consent before collecting or using information for a purpose other than those that are set out in this Privacy Policy.

Information we collect

• Device information. We may collect device-specific information, such as your hardware model, operating system version, device ID (persistent/non-persistent), Media access control (“MAC”) address, international mobile equipment identity (“IMEI”)
• Application information. We may collect information about your installation, such us the operating system type and application version number.
• Information you give us. When you contact AMG, we may keep a record of your communication to help solve any issues you might be facing. We may use your email address to inform you about our services, such as letting you know about upcoming changes or improvements.
• Third-party services. We may use third-party services to help us understand the use of our Service, such as Google Analytics. These third-party service providers may collect information sent by your browser as part of a web page request, such as cookies, your IP address, browser type, domain name, access times, referring website addresses. AMG may also collect your email address (if you have connected to Facebook, Apple’s Game Center, Google+ or other social networks), and your location (based on your IP address).
This information is gathered to provide general statistics regarding the Sites and/or Games and to enhance your online experience.
Information we don’t collect

AMG does not automatically collect personally identifiable information, such as your name, address, or e-mail address, from your visit to the Sites and/or Games

Information we share

We do not share or disclose your private personal information unless necessary to comply with a law, regulation or legal request.
We may share or disclose your non-private, aggregated or otherwise non-personal information, such as aggregate usage statistics.

