Use of Cookies

The AMG Websites may use “cookies” to help you personalize your online experience. Cookies are pieces of information that a website transfers to an individual’s computer hard drive for record keeping purposes. Cookies are uniquely assigned to you, are restricted for use only on the Sites, and do not transfer any personal information to any other party. Cookies cannot be used to run programs or deliver viruses to your computer. One of the primary purposes of cookies is to provide a convenience feature to save you time by, among other things, saving your preferences for you and helping AMG to recall your specific information on subsequent visits. You have the ability to accept or decline cookies. Most Web browsers automatically accept cookies, but you can reset your browser to refuse all cookies or indicate when a cookie is being sent. If you choose to disable your cookies setting or refuse to accept a cookie, some parts of the AMG websites may not function properly or may considerably slower.

Children Age 13 and Under

AMG does not knowingly collect or solicit personally identifiable information from children under the age of thirteen. If you are under the age of thirteen, you must ask your parent or guardian for permission to use the AMG Sites and/or the Games and we request that you do not submit any personal information including your name, address, telephone number, or email address to the AMG Websites and/or the Games. 
It is important that you understand that AMG may use social networks in the Websites and/or Games to allow users who are 13 years old or older to have fun by exchanging their gameplay events with other users over the age of 13. The Social Networks AMG uses are based on prominent third party social networks, like Facebook, Apple’s Game Center, Google+ and etc. AMG relies on the age restrictions from these networks to make sure only users over the age of 13 can share information. 
If AMG finds that personal information from a child under age thirteen is collected, AMG will delete that information as quickly as possible. If you believe that AMG might have any information from or about children under age thirteen, please contact us at antonmakegames@gmail.com.

